US genealogy expert Megan Smolenyak has traced Hillary Clinton to a poor mining family from Ystradyfodwg in the Welsh Valleys . 
  Her great-grandmother Hannah Jones emigrated to America with her family in 1871 . 
  She and her husband Hugh Rodham eloped to Binghampton in New York . 
  Mary Griffiths Jones was born in Merthyr Tydfil and lived in poverty . 
  Mrs Clinton's family were from the mining district which is now part of Rhondda . 
 